    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I do think it would make our API more complex (from a user POV) to have something like:\n\n``` js\nwidgets.headLess.searchBox\n```\n\nor\n\n``` js\ninstantsearch(appId, apiKey, {searchBox:}\n```\n\n(also this second proposal from @redox does not allow the user to put multiple searchBox, something people will do at some point)\n\nVersus just having:\n\n``` js\nwidgets.searchBox\n```\n\nWhy would we distinguish the searchBox from other widgets only because we do not insert markup in it?. What level of information it brings to the API user?\n\nEven if we do not insert markup we are going to do a LOT of DOM: bind event handlers, change placeholder, change the value of the input.\n\nAs a user I know that using instantsearch.js will do DOM manipulation. If you warn me that \"The searchBox widgets works by enhancing the `<input>` you provide\" Then I am allright, that's all I need to know.\n\n**To summarize**: `searchBox` IS a widget, it's just an empty element that we do DOM manipulation on it, no need to complexify the API for this implementation detail that we can express in plain words in the documentation.\n\nTrying to put a one line documentation detail into our API design will result in more complexity and incomprehension from users.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-08-06T12:40:12Z",
